How to create volker reports?

Source: vignettes/reports.Rmd
reports.Rmd

Reports combine graphs, tables, indexes and additional output.´ The volker package comes with a Markdown template that generates interactive HTML documents in which you can switch between the different parts of the report.

How to use the template: - Create a new R Markdown document from the menu - Select “From template”

Alternatively, manually add volker::html_report to the output options of your Markdown document:

---
title: "How to create reports?"
output: 
  volker::html_report
---

Then, you can generate combined outputs using the report-functions. One advantage of the report-functions is that plots are automatically scaled to fit the page.

A single categorical variable 

report_counts(data, sd_gender)

A cross table 

data %>% 
  filter(sd_gender != "diverse") %>%
  filter(adopter != "I only use new offers when I have no other choice") %>% 
  report_counts(adopter, sd_gender, prop="rows", title="Innovator")

Mix in your own content

If you want to add content before the outputs, set the title parameter to FALSE and add your own title.

A good place for methodological details is a tabsheet next to the “Plot” and the “Table” buttons. You can add a tab by setting the close-parameter to FALSE and adding a new header on the fifth level (5 x # followed by the tab name). Close your new tabsheet with #### {-} (4 x #). See the example Markdown behind this vignette.

Adoption types 
data %>% 
  filter(sd_gender != "diverse") %>% 
  filter(adopter != "I only use new offers when I have no other choice") %>% 
  report_counts(adopter, sd_gender, prop="rows", title= FALSE, close= FALSE, effect=T)
